This paper deals with theoretical aspects of database query optimization, specifically in the context of relational joins. The paper discusses worst-case and average-case models for estimating join sizes and finding good execution plans, which are core topics in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also uses combinatorial techniques to analyze hypergraphs, which is a common tool in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses density measures of hypergraphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT).
